description: Violet's supernaturally unstable condition is exposed when it pops out and bites her on the...
name: Screaming Habdabs

description: Shrieking Violet encounters the Witchgrinder... cue upside-down kinky brainsex overload!
name: Chronic Luscious

description: long comes a Splinter Man. Don't worry, it'll only hurt for a second.
name: Splinters

description: She's worn the hat and talked the talk, but can she wear the face and look the look?
name: Bondoo Night

description: Violet's in the kitchen with with a daring new recipe... for disaster.
name: Black and Blue

description: Blonde, bothered and bewildered. Violet's caught with her pants down again, and finds herself playing the unlikely role of traditional style scream queen.
name: Fusion Blonde

description: Now that she's in possession of an ecto-morphic occult secret weapon, how far is Violet prepared to go to track down the mysterious Elastic Head?
name: Pod

description: Violet dabbles with rock 'n' roll magick to try and shake up her love life.
name: Souled Out

description: Backed by ancient magicks, stinky skunkdevils, and swarms of gnashing teeth, Violet sets out to get her groove back.
name: 30 Miles of Bad Road

description: More trouble at the House of Grimm! The deranged doll named Dolores Twist tempts Violet into donning a slimy artifact found lying dormant under the stairs. Before the shivers can even finish rippling down her back, Violet begins to hear creepy noises echoing through her home. A voice from beyond signals the imminent arrival of a mysterious (and, as is the Dogwitch standard, undoubtedly kinky) houseguest. To make it through the day with dignity intact, Violet's going to have to relax and slide with it. Either that or go crazy with power tools.
name: Tentacles

description: Violet Grimm's cringing beneath the stairs, crazy flashbacks flooding her mind. Dolores, the scarred living doll, is acting stranger than usual. With ouija boards exploding and the dead sending text messages, you know that something bad is going down. Does Violet's back-from-the-dead sister Bluebell have the answer, or is she part of the problem? What's hidden in the attic? And what really happened at the first (and lethally last) Vile Ettes rock concert? Prepare for shocking revelations in the Season 2 finale!
name: Pretty Like Drugs

description: Thought the last issue was a shocker? Dont get too comfortable. There may be more surprises in store. Violets back, and she is not happy! Still reeling from betrayal and mad mojo, she now faces more trouble in the form of a bizarre allergy to the psychic fallout from Dolores spell. Violet needs a doctor, but what the hell kind of doctor will make a call out to the middle of the Banewoods? Enter: the Fetish Nurse!
name: Pumpkins

description: There's something on the tape! The video recording of the Vile Ettes rock concert holds a secret. Something that no one has noticed. Want to know who was responsible for the violent death of Bluebell? And why?
name: Clockwork Candy

description: What are little girls made of? Take a peek at the twisted originof Violet Grimm, courtesy of the Toxic Spring of Illumination. Packed to the brim with everything you ever wanted to know about Violets past, this is a dive straight to the bottom.Take a deep breath,theyll be no coming up for air until its all over.
name: Illuminator

description: She's wet, she's hungry, she's ankle deep in dead meat, and she's missed her own coming-out party. So why is she smiling? More revelations in this issue as Violet discovers the truth about the Black Treacle.
name: Blasphemy

description: Ralph's found a way to look into the past, but there's no time for re-runs, Elastic Head's on the warpath and out for revenge. Violet's posse don't do housework, but can they do teamwork?
name: Peepshow

description: Violet Grimm has returned to the Nice Bunny World to face off with those responsible for banishing her to the Banewoods. With Mr. Kinky playing sidekick, shes on a mission to expose The Order, and reveal and elaborate cosmic conspiracy. But theres a surprise in store for her that could finally tip her over the edge, and to confront her biggest personal demon, shes going to have to sacrifice more than her little finger. Violet has come home, and shes going to make a mess!
name: Missy Aggrevation

description: Luse, Luce and Jace attempt to escape the city but are found out by the police. Talon also confronts Luse and Jace. Tenth and Hyena send Mishah to find Lusiphur.
name: Two: Out of the Bag

description: Tenth and Hyena sends Mishah to rescue Luse and Jace. When she finds them shes cast a spell which doesn't have the effects it should have.
name: Three: Cat's Cradle

description: Morachi has decided the best way to get to Luse is to release the E'jja which makes Fleece and Serendeh quit Sanctuary. Luse is dealing with being a woman. Men hitting on shim and dealing with other womanly things like high heels and oh look you got your monthly visit.
name: Four: Like Cats and Dogs

description: While still trying to get out of town Luse and Jace run into Friedrich and Balinarch also trying to get out of town. Then along comes the Purple Marauder...Very funny Dawn parody on the back cover.
name: Five: On a Hot Tin Roof

description: Luse and Jace and Friedrich and Balinarch still trying to get out of town when Luse is knocked out and sent to visit Parintachin who informs him to not ditch Jace as he will forever be on his side and we get to see what Parintachin really is...
name: Six: Strays

story_arc_credits.name: Sanctuary Book 6: Cat and Mouse One: Here Kitty Kitty

description: Morachi lets the E'jja out and its not good times at Sanctuary and Serendeh, Fleece and Dendrin make it out. The E'jja heads off after Luse. Jace and Luse fight their way out of town and make it with the help of the Purple Marauder!?! Luse finds himself back to being a man but leaves Lirilith hanging which Parintachin told hime woulr regret for the rest of his life.
name: Sanctuary Book 7: End One: The Way We Were

description: Cleah debuts by trying to capture and/or kill Luse and Jace in the process cutting off one of Jace's ears. Luse fights her off and dumps her over a cliff.
name: The Collector

description: Tenth decides to mess with Jace and Luse and sends animated boots to attack them. Just for fun.
name: Night of the Living Boots

description: Luse and Jace enter the town of Pike and find out they have a werewolf problem. They search out the mayor to try to get the werewolf slaying job but find out they hired a werewolf hunter by the name of Winston. After besting her they are given contract to kill the wolf but there's one catch they have only four nights to do it.
name: Just In Town For A Bite

description: After getting their butts handed to them by the werewolf. Luse has caught the disease as well and is now trying to hide it. The mayor assigns Winston to help them but the town folk feel they found their werewolf. Jasper Dar the Mayor's daughter's fiancee.
name: Things That Go Ripping Your Head Off In The Dead Of Night

description: The boys and Winston team up to capture the werewolf but it turns out to be someone who will cause more trouble than good...the mayors daughter!!! Needless to say the three of them were run out of town for even suggesting this.
name: Unt Der Verevolf Iss...

description: After escaping Pike, Luse, Jace and Winston are camping when Luse starts seeing Cassy. It ends up being a sprite named Petunia and is soon followed by a giant! With Luse's aide Petunia dispatches the giant and earns her wings. Plus it appears Petunia has a little crush on Luse.
name: Petunia

description: Winston goes off on here own and the boys tell Petunia that if she can clear out a bar she can stay. She dispatches the entire bar quickly. Then Luse beats up a mime and I think himself I'm not really sure.
name: 3 Hits From Hell

description: Petunia sees Parintachin inside Luse's head and flies in to kick him out. The argue over what's best for him and decide that Petunia gets the outside and Parintachin gets the inside.
name: The Dark...

description: First we are treated to a little of Jace's past, Then we see the boys trying to figure out a way to make money. They are hired onto the Mary Brine to guard whatever is behind that locked door.
name: Give Em

description: Well they failed at guard duty and awaken to find everyone on the ship dead. Cleah is the captain of the boat that boarded and stole the cargo and slaughtered the rest of the people on the boat.
name: Seaferring

description: Cleah brings the boys aboard her ship and plan on killing them but Luse and Jace get the upper hand and they find out what the cargo was...the elven ember the last of the Elven Fire! Now Jace wants to sell it and Cleah wants to protect it. Its up to Luse to be the deciding vote.
name: Runnin' With The Devil

description: Deciding to return the Elven Fire to the elves, our elven friends are on the run from the Dark Army. Camping at night they are awakened by a ROARGH!. They bust out of the tent to find a large skeletal monster tromping through the forrest. Discussing whether the monster was after them it attacked. The found that their blade simple busted againt it except for Luse's magical blade but he doesn't know how to use it. Luse grabs the fire and runs and comes up with a plan with sketches and everything that would make Jay and Silent Bob envious. The plan doesn't work and while fleeing across a bridge it falls and Luse and the monster with it. Luse out of desperation smacked the monster with the flame catching it on fire. The beast burned as Luse wondered why Cleah got such a stupid haircut.
name: Nemisis

description: While walking through the forest Luse decides to eat some mushrooms which are a bit magic. As he is tripping he thoroughly insult Cleah about selling out the elven race. She storms off and Jace orders him to go apologize. When Luse leave Jace is confronted bt Cassy who he fight and finds out it was a doppelganger. As it disappears Luse find Cleah and sorta apologizes. Good thing cause there's an E'jja behind you.
name: Day of the Doppelganger

description: Luse begins the fight with Widowmaker sending Cleah to fetch Jace. Luse's sword protects him against the E'jja until Jace and Cleah return. Jace figures out that it is not the real E'jja but a doppelganger. Luse and his sword make short work of it and the team continues on.
name: Love Me Tender, Love Me True - Beat Me Till I'm Black & Blue

description: Luse and company are making their way to the First Step but are cut off by a Dark Troll. Luse sends Jace and Cleah ahead with the Fire while tries to kill the dark troll. Running out of options Luse decides its also thime for him to run!
name: Higher Evolutions

description: While running from the Dark Troll Luse rounds a corner to see Mogre-Ur. Mogre-Ur is believed to be the oldest most powerful elf alive. Mogre-Ur help Luse fight off the troll while Jace and Cleah are being guarded by elven troops. They escape the guards and head to help Luse. They arrive just in time to see Luse get knocked out and Mogre-Ur pop the trolls head off. Luse awakens to Parintachin who has had a little company...Petunia!
name: The Worm, The Wizard, The Solider, The Rake...

description: Luse is back inside his head with Parintachin and now Petunia. While they were waiting Parintachin build a Dreamcast and used Soul Calibur to teach Petunia to speak Amrhallic (common). Par then give Luse a history lesson about creation and Cinlach Luse's magical sword. Luse finally awakens in First Step Prison.
name: I Must Not Think Bad Thoughts...

description: While waiting in first step prison Luse and Jace meet the wild man Chowmba. Cleah also explains they're there because of Luse's killing of a high council member and Jace is being considered an accomplice. Mogre-Ur and Cleah both hint that Luse and Jace should escape and Chowmba joins them.
name: Chowmba

description: Our guys are held up in a tower with the Elvin Fire in Mogre-Ur's estate tossing books are innocent passer-bys. As a Elvin High Council meeting is ending we meet Stefani Gwen another member of the council as they discuss the fate of Luse and Jace. Mogre-Ur is appointed negotiator by the High Council playing into their plans.

Lusiphur is visited by a messanger in his dreams. it takes many forms the Purple Marauder, Six Tell, and finally settling on Cassy. It explains some stuff to Luse before being awakened by Mogre-Ur. Mogre-Ur gives them the only deal they can get. They work for him, commit no more crimes, and their records are cleared. What's an elf to do?

Luse and Jace are charged with escorting Wisp a one of a kind elvin psyonicist to Sanrova for training and then escort the trainers daughter to the First Step. But Wisp isn't exactly your normal little elf.
name: Albino Voodooconda

description:
A tale written and drawn by the Fillbach Brothers in continuity it falls after Issue 41 and before the "Hell Hath No Fury" story in the Poison Elves Color Special.

Luse and Jace tired of walking through the woods decide to go to the nearest town for food, rest and a beer. Upon entering town they notice that its kind of quit. They enter the pub order up some food that is a little rotten. They then noticed the zombies. They end up unconsious and Luse went into his head to se Parintachin who informed him that it wasn't Drew Hayes in command but two other people the Fillbach Brothers. He then informed Luse that he, the Purple Marauder and Drew Hayes were going for a beer and he was on his own. Waking up Luse wakes Jace up and they were captured by Dr. Shithound. He's your garden variety mad scientist who created the zombies. The doctor wants to experiment on them but they are saved by one of his experiments, Mugaluna, who rescues our heroes. The doctor then mutates and once again Mugaluna sacrfices herself to save Jace and Luse.
name: All The Beautiful People or: Bad Doin's At Knuckledown Lonesome

description:
Continued from issue 60.

Luse and Jace are escorting Wisp when the here some dogs and a hunting horn. It turns out to be a Huntsman sent for them. They end up hiding and waiting for him to leave...but did he really leave. NEXT ISSUE BOB THE FREEBOOTER!
name: The Hunt

description: Luse, Jace, and Wisp decide to stay in the tourist trap Avalanche. While there they meet a convenience store worker named Bob. He's a uber-depressed "minimum wage bitch". Luse, Jace, and Wisp went to the store and Bob had dispatched a few robbers and decided to quit and join them on their quest. The a E'jja attacks and Luse informs Bob that he'll wish for his job back.
name: Suicide Bob

description: Bob, Jace, and Luse fight off the E'jja until Luse decides its time for Wisp to use his powers. Luse runs to Wisp but breaks his ankle in the process and calls for the E'jja to come get Wisp and forcing Wisp to use his power that he's scared of to find the one single way to kill it.
name: Killing An E'jja

description: Luse and Jace are kicked out of Avalanche due to their fight with the E'jja. Luse with a broken ankle and Jace with a nasty cold, Wisp out cold over Jace's shoulder. They wonder upon an old house. They go in to get out of the could then the house starts playing with their heads. Wisp wakes up to realize it was his power that turned the house alive. He immediately explodes the house leaving a large crater and destroying the house.
name: Bauhaus

description: .The boys enter Keyerney during the Festival of Goblins and decide to have a few drink...well a lot of drinks. They get drunk and lose Wisp to some goblins and the Huntsman.
name: Bad Fun

description: Luse uses his new found connections from working for the High Council while Jace sleeps off his hangover. We find out Morlagan has kidnapped Wisp.
name: Elves of Constant Sorrow

description: Luse and Jace infiltrate where they are holding Wisp. Jace gets severly wounded and orders Luse to retreat and get them some help. Luse escapes by wearing some goblin armor and decides to recruit some friends to help free Jace and Wisp.
name: Crossroad

description: Going through Wiccalow Luse runs into the thief Lynn who knows everything about him and wants him to train her. He laughs find out she only has killed a few people. Luse is betayed by his ranger skills and falls down a hill right in front of the McGorsky Clan. He is knocked out and meets Parintachin who pretty much tells him to stop being a lackey.
name: The Clan

description:
Luse wakes up in in Briney Cove home of the redneck hillbillies the McGorsky Clan. Luse is being lined up to be killed when Lynn attacks and rescues him. At this point the story ends and various PE characters tell us that Drew Hayes has been sick and hospitalized and that he should fully recover.

This was the beginning of Drew's health problems.
name: Home Sick Home

description: Luse and Lynn hike their way towards a castle. They find the castle as it appears at sundown. Inside they run into Mishah who Luse immediately shoots in the chest explaining to Lynn that she would turn her into a woman. Luse now knows that Tenth is there and instructs Lynn to wait there while he goes to find him. He finds Tenth in bad shape. Lynn sees Mishah start to get up. Mishah notices she is a woman and figures if Luse would shoot her on sight she must be bad news and starts to fight her. Luse gets a little to close to Tenth which some how turns off the curse Hyena put on him.
name: Down By The Sea

description: Petunia delivers Lusiphur's request to Lirilith. Wisp gives into Morlagan. Luse & Lynn fight some goblins.Mogre-Ur and the Elvin Council seek passage and use of the human cities and fort during the coming war.
name: Cohesions II

description: Lynn finally tell Luse the she's a girl and Luse makes some comment which sends Lynn off the end. Lynn and Luse wonder into some druidic ruins. Lynn being a virgin sets off the the ruins and release the Slaughter Daughters. Luse and Lynn are getting beat down while Luse screams for Tenth who arrives and freezes the daughters. Tenth sends them to where Hyena is but get there and when they appear Lynn is no longer a virgin.
name: Day of the Slaughter Daughters

description: One of the longest-lived, greatest comics in history comes to BOOM! Studios! A direct market event -- the title that was host to Walt Disney's most cherished characters that helped build a decades-spanning global empire, originally launched in 1942, has come to BOOM! Kids! Ever wondered what would happen when all the superheroes of the Disney comics universe star in an epic clash against all the super villains with the fate of the world at stake? Join The Duck Avenger, Super Goofy, and the man himself Mickey Mouse for an all-new team of heroes, an all-new era in Disney publishing!

"The Beauty of Decay" Part 3! Fig, Peter and Jordan venture out into the city of ghosts to visit the long-abandoned Pathfinder's Academy where the most desperate specters wail and gnash. But the Pathfinder's Academy holds more than ghosts - it also contains ancient dark secrets that will change Fig's life forever. Featuring guest art by Werther Dell'Edera (LOVELESS) and a special tale of Fig Keele: "Teen Detective" by SWEET TOOTH creator and Xeric, Alex and Shuster Award-winner Jeff Lemire (THE NOBODY, The Essex County Trilogy).
name: Academics: Part Three of the Beauty of Decay; The Tale of Brutus the Bold

description: Continuing the chronicle of the Marvel Universe, starting with Spider-Man (from AMAZING SPIDER-MAN #429 on), Iron Man (from IRON MAN ANNUAL 1999 on) and the X-Men (from UNCANNY X-MEN #416 on). Follow the history of the Marvel universe as it unfolds month by month with the All-New Official Index to the Marvel Universe. Each issue provides synopses for dozens of individual comics, including back-up strips, introducing you to the characters, teams, places and equipment that appeared within, providing vital information about first appearances, where they last showed up and where they appeared next!
name: Volume Ten

description: The resurrection of the Torch! The Mad Thinker proceeds with his investigation into the Jim Hammond's nature and origin, in order to rebuild him and put him in the service of A.I.M. But the Thinker's true goals go far beyond his brief, and in his hands, all knowledge is power.

The bombastic saga rolls on! Tony Stark FINALLY has his IRON MAN armor back...good thing, too, 'cuz there's about three dozen assassins with orders to take him dead or alive...

We start at an underground facility where the Red Barbarian resurrects Omega Red by sacrificing Ursa Major. Meanwhile Iron Man and James Rhode continue their escape from the army on a stolen plane which is taken down. Iron Man takes Rhodes to safety and after theirs pursuer helicopter receive some damage Iron man comes to the rescue.

iron Man continues to a missile silo where he finds several armors and enemies waiting for him.
name: How I Learned to Love the Bomb
